The paper discusses a novel algorithm for searching for short patterns over long texts, which is a fundamental task in bioinformatics. The paper specifically focuses on compressed full-text indexes, which are widely used in bioinformatics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the algorithm in practice, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) or cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses information retrieval and data mining techniques, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.DM (Data Mining).
